- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper mentions that the coloring of digraphs corresponds naturally to an automaton, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses the road coloring theorem, which is a result in logic and graph theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the properties of digraphs and their colorings, which are important concepts in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper mentions the concept of synchronizing coloring, which is related to the study of games on graphs in game theory.
